article.headline: W. Kentucky 81, Louisiana-Monroe 61
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- Sergio Kerusch and Juan Pattillo had 17 points each to lead Western Kentucky to an 81-61 victory over Louisiana-Monroe on Saturday. Trailing 7-6, the Hilltoppers (10-12, 5-5 Sun Belt Conference) went on a 14-0 run and led the rest of the way by as much as 22 points. They shot 27 of 53 from the field and the Warhawks (6-19, 1-10) were 22 of 51. Pattillo came off the bench to go 6 for 6 and Kerusch was 6 of 13 from the field. Kerusch also had a game-high 13 rebounds for his seventh double-double in nine games. Western Kentucky outrebounded Louisiana-Monroe 37-27 and the Hilltoppers' bench outscored Louisiana-Monroe's bench 34-12. Steffphon Pettigrew chipped in 16 points for the Hilltoppers, who are 1-1 on their five-game homestand. Fred Brown led the Warhawks, who have lost six consecutive games, with 16 points and Lawrence Gilbert added 13.
